{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17513918","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17513918"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:16:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:16:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12250"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12250","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12250"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.07,0.81,0.03,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4772"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116468"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4772"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12250"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98467"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1793"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7606"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7633"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26767"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116468","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116468"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA patient has recently been diagnosed with ovarian cancer and will be starting a carboplatin-based chemotherapy regimen.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Monitoring of which one of the following serum markers is most appropriate in this case?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Carcinoembryonic antigen (CEA)","Carbohydrate antigen 19-9 (CA-19-9)","Cancer antigen 125 (CA-125)","Alpha-fetoprotein (AFP)","Human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG)"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum cancer antigen 125 (CA125)\u003C/strong\u003E is widely used in ovarian cancer to monitor the effectiveness of therapy both in first line and recurrence. It is also widely used during follow-up, where it is able to identify a percentage of patients with asymptomatic recurrence. The absolute level of CA125 before therapy has also been shown to be of prognostic importance. Moreover, the serum half-life of CA125 during initial chemotherapy has been shown to be an independent prognostic marker for survival, rate of progression, time to progression, and the chance to achieve complete remission.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoembryonic antigen (CEA)\u003C/strong\u003E is a large glycoprotein, and its serum measurement is helpful in managing gastrointestinal and pancreatic cancers. It can also be elevated in smoking and other benign conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarbohydrate antigen 19-9 (CA-19-9)\u003C/strong\u003E is most useful in the management of patients with adenocarcinoma of the pancreas. It has been found \u003Cem\u003Enot\u003C/em\u003E to be helpful in patients with colon cancer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha-fetoprotein (AFP)\u003C/strong\u003E is an onco-developmental antigen that was one of the first tumor markers used in clinical practice. It is expressed in the fetus and is elevated in the serum of patients with hepatocellular\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Ecarcinoma, not ovarian cancer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHuman chorionic gonadotropin (hCG)\u003C/strong\u003E is produced during pregnancy. Elevated levels are seen with pregnancy and with HCG-secreting tumors.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cancer antigen 125 (CA125) is widely used as a biomarker for evaluating disease status and monitoring the efficacy of chemotherapy in patients with epithelial ovarian cancer (EOC).","CA125 levels can provide prognostic information and help in detecting asymptomatic recurrence in ovarian cancer."],"references":["Lee M, Chang MY, Yoo H, Lee KE, Chay DB, Cho H, Kim S, Kim YT, Kim JH. Clinical Significance of CA125 Level after the First Cycle of Chemotherapy on Survival of Patients with Advanced Ovarian Cancer. Yonsei Med J. 2016 May;57(3):580-7. doi: 10.3349/ymj.2016.57.3.580. PMID: 26996555; PMCID: PMC4800345. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26996555/","Charkhchi P, Cybulski C, Gronwald J, Wong FO, Narod SA, Akbari MR. CA125 and Ovarian Cancer: A Comprehensive Review. Cancers (Basel). 2020 Dec 11;12(12):3730. doi: 10.3390/cancers12123730. PMID: 33322519; PMCID: PMC7763876. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33322519/","Funston G, Mounce LT, Price S, Rous B, Crosbie EJ, Hamilton W, Walter FM. CA125 test result, test-to-diagnosis interval, and stage in ovarian cancer at diagnosis: a retrospective cohort study using electronic health records. Br J Gen Pract. 2021 May 27;71(707):e465-e472. doi: 10.3399/BJGP.2020.0859. PMID: 33875416; PMCID: PMC8074643. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8074643/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98467"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12250"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98467","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98467"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-29T10:36:24+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-29T10:36:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4772"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116468"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"